00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Subtitles by KBS World 

2
00:00:23,940 --> 00:00:25,820
It's yummy. 

3
00:00:25,820 --> 00:00:27,320
The flavors are alive. 

4
00:00:29,040 --> 00:00:32,680
My lovely brother, did you enjoy that? 

5
00:00:32,940 --> 00:00:35,450
Be yourself. You're creeping me out. 

6
00:00:36,650 --> 00:00:38,490
Why did you drop out of school? 

7
00:00:38,490 --> 00:00:40,220
Uh, how did you find out? 

8
00:00:41,170 --> 00:00:43,210
Oh, my homeroom... 

9
00:00:43,210 --> 00:00:44,450
Does the geezer know? 

10
00:00:45,410 --> 00:00:47,770
Geezer? How dare you! He's your dad! 

11
00:00:47,770 --> 00:00:50,380
All the kids call him the geezer. 

12
00:00:50,380 --> 00:00:52,640
If I don't call him that, they'll find out. 

13
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:54,730
Nobody at school knows you're his son? 

14
00:00:54,970 --> 00:00:55,870
Nope. 

15
00:00:57,170 --> 00:00:58,560
Who was that truck guy? 

16
00:00:58,560 --> 00:01:00,870
You want to know?
It'll cost you 50 cents. 

17
00:01:00,870 --> 00:01:02,100
I said who is he? 

18
00:01:03,470 --> 00:01:10,390
Must you bring that up at a local pizzeria where they serve delicious pizza? 

19
00:01:10,390 --> 00:01:13,170
Why are you following a stranger around? 

20
00:01:13,170 --> 00:01:14,950
What if he's a human trafficker? 

21
00:01:14,950 --> 00:01:16,420
What if he makes you beg for money? 

22
00:01:16,420 --> 00:01:17,890
What if he sells you to a shrimp ship? 

23
00:01:17,890 --> 00:01:20,700
I'm not a kid.
Don't you know me at all? 

24
00:01:20,700 --> 00:01:22,650
Don't you feel bad for dad? 

25
00:01:22,650 --> 00:01:25,390
I said I'll hold his memorial services! 

26
00:01:25,390 --> 00:01:26,560
So what's the problem here? 

27
00:01:26,560 --> 00:01:28,070
It's not the memorial services I'm worried about. 

28
00:01:28,070 --> 00:01:31,290
Look at uncle, your second brother in law and me! 

29
00:01:31,290 --> 00:01:33,390
How do you think our family will turn out? 

30
00:01:33,390 --> 00:01:34,710
Really messed up? 

31
00:01:35,290 --> 00:01:36,330
Incredible. 

32
00:01:38,580 --> 00:01:40,100
Give me Truck's number. 

33
00:01:40,620 --> 00:01:41,940
I don't know the truck's number. 

34
00:01:41,940 --> 00:01:44,160
I mean the truck owner's number. 

35
00:01:44,160 --> 00:01:46,130
- Dream on.
- What? 

36
00:01:46,130 --> 00:01:48,120
Don't you ever look in the mirror? 

37
00:01:48,120 --> 00:01:49,620
He's way out of your league. 

38
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:55,820
Ouch, man... 

39
00:01:55,820 --> 00:01:58,730
Excuse me, you shouldn't do that here. 

40
00:02:01,240 --> 00:02:03,600
Really? They found her? 

41
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:05,680
It's not 100%. 

42
00:02:05,680 --> 00:02:07,530
They said they'll call me tomorrow. 

43
00:02:08,310 --> 00:02:10,400
I tried so hard, but I couldn't find her. 

44
00:02:11,210 --> 00:02:14,740
I looked for her for 3 years in Geoje-do Island. 

45
00:02:15,710 --> 00:02:17,580
Auntie, don't tell father. 

46
00:02:17,580 --> 00:02:20,420
I won't. He'd kick me out if he knew. 

47
00:02:20,420 --> 00:02:24,740
I really hope you find her this time. 

48
00:02:26,090 --> 00:02:29,740
You should meet with her at least once. 

49
00:02:29,740 --> 00:02:32,990
Meet with her and get it off your chest. 

50
00:02:39,410 --> 00:02:41,000
- You're home.
- Yes. 

51
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,580
Daese, did you have dinner? 

52
00:02:42,580 --> 00:02:44,530
I ate already. 

53
00:02:44,530 --> 00:02:49,710
Oh, my doctor said not to touch this part. 

54
00:02:52,620 --> 00:02:55,930
Oh, I'm furious.
I should be better by now. 

55
00:02:55,930 --> 00:02:58,000
So rude!
Wait until I meet her again! 

56
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:00,000
- Who?
- You don't know her. 

57
00:03:00,340 --> 00:03:02,580
Oh, what happened with Mr. Kim? 

58
00:03:02,580 --> 00:03:05,870
It's not broken, but he pulled a ligament. 

59
00:03:05,870 --> 00:03:08,510
He was lucky. 

60
00:03:08,510 --> 00:03:11,230
My skin's all rough,  

61
00:03:11,230 --> 00:03:13,930
and my emotions are also all rough... Ugh. 

62
00:03:15,540 --> 00:03:18,590
Would you like to go to Jeju-do Island after this? 

63
00:03:18,590 --> 00:03:19,840
We can play golf. 

64
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:22,630
You can go to the spa and get a massage. 

65
00:03:22,630 --> 00:03:24,910
Hey, let's play for money. 

66
00:03:24,910 --> 00:03:26,630
Let's not let the other get off easy. 

67
00:03:26,630 --> 00:03:28,640
I've been getting real good distance, 

68
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:30,370
since I have nowhere else to use my energy. 

69
00:03:30,370 --> 00:03:33,270
That means nothing. You must finish well. 

70
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:38,040
Like this! 

71
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:40,890
Yes! Ouch, ouch... 

72
00:04:03,390 --> 00:04:08,550
Play with me.
Play with me and my doll. 

73
00:04:08,550 --> 00:04:10,250
Oh, man! 

74
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:12,120
Play with me, mom. 

75
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:13,330
Ugh! Get away from me! 

76
00:04:13,330 --> 00:04:15,900
- Play with me!
- You're so annoying! 

77
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:23,210
Okay, next!
Bangtong, you're done! Yes. 

78
00:04:23,210 --> 00:04:27,630
Get dressed. Let's make rice rolls and go visit your granddad at his school. 

79
00:04:27,630 --> 00:04:29,660
Yay! Nice! 

80
00:04:29,660 --> 00:04:31,600
Oh, but it's Sunday. 

81
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:33,420
He goes to school, even on Sundays. 

82
00:04:33,420 --> 00:04:35,760
Mom, let's go to the amusement park. 

83
00:04:35,760 --> 00:04:37,590
All my friends have gone. 

84
00:04:37,590 --> 00:04:39,110
Ugh! 

85
00:04:39,110 --> 00:04:40,690
You know how expensive that is? 

86
00:04:40,690 --> 00:04:42,780
You think money grows on trees? 

87
00:04:42,780 --> 00:04:44,340
We will go. 

88
00:04:44,340 --> 00:04:45,570
When? When? 

89
00:04:45,570 --> 00:04:47,410
When we move to an apartment. 

90
00:04:47,410 --> 00:04:49,360
Then I'll take you to the amusement park. 

91
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:50,870
And buy you pizza, too! 

92
00:04:50,870 --> 00:04:52,680
I'd grow old and die before then! 

93
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:54,150
How rude! 

94
00:04:54,150 --> 00:04:56,140
I'm older than you,
but I'm saying nothing. 

95
00:05:03,670 --> 00:05:04,620
Mom. 

96
00:05:04,620 --> 00:05:07,510
Lucky you.
You can make money. 

97
00:05:08,210 --> 00:05:09,230
Make money? 

98
00:05:09,230 --> 00:05:10,740
Go to your sister's place. 

99
00:05:10,740 --> 00:05:12,770
Her housekeeper quit. 

100
00:05:12,770 --> 00:05:13,750
Why? 

101
00:05:17,700 --> 00:05:20,280
- Auntie.
- Aeji, poor baby. 

102
00:05:20,280 --> 00:05:22,110
Auntie will play with you. 

103
00:05:24,080 --> 00:05:25,590
Why did she quit? 

104
00:05:25,590 --> 00:05:26,830
I don't know. 

105
00:05:27,890 --> 00:05:30,130
He fired her without talking to me. 

106
00:05:31,150 --> 00:05:32,300
Minjung did? 

107
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:33,800
He told me to do the housekeeping! 

108
00:05:34,540 --> 00:05:38,330
I yelled at him because of my credit cards. 

109
00:05:38,330 --> 00:05:40,600
No, I can finally breathe. 

110
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:43,240
I can't take care of my children. 

111
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:55,390
Oh, Jungji, you're precious. 

112
00:06:07,070 --> 00:06:08,130
Oh, you're so good. 

113
00:06:08,130 --> 00:06:10,790
- Sintong, stop!
- No way. 

114
00:06:12,190 --> 00:06:14,890
Grandpa, I can't catch him. 

115
00:06:15,280 --> 00:06:17,100
Sintong, stop! 

116
00:06:18,910 --> 00:06:21,210
It'd be fun to go as couples. 

117
00:06:21,860 --> 00:06:24,600
When you go into the blue waters of Maldives, 

118
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:27,020
oh, it's like heaven. 

119
00:06:27,020 --> 00:06:29,860
Guam's nice, too, and we can go shopping. 

120
00:06:29,860 --> 00:06:31,520
Or should we go to Hong Kong? 

121
00:06:31,840 --> 00:06:33,790
That must really hurt. 

122
00:06:33,790 --> 00:06:36,260
Be careful not to bump into anything. 

123
00:06:44,020 --> 00:06:45,940
Oh, no... 

124
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:58,270
A woman? 

125
00:06:58,270 --> 00:06:59,440
Is there proof? 

126
00:06:59,440 --> 00:07:01,400
I have a feeling. 

127
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:03,220
Minjung isn't the type. 

128
00:07:04,020 --> 00:07:05,990
You can never be sure. 

129
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:10,180
Anyway, Aeji seems to have lost weight. 

130
00:07:10,180 --> 00:07:11,700
She's beyond picky about her food. 

131
00:07:11,700 --> 00:07:13,920
And Jungji's so cranky at bedtime. 

132
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:15,830
Both girls are so difficult. 

133
00:07:15,830 --> 00:07:18,850
Rich children are supposed to be difficult. 

134
00:07:18,850 --> 00:07:22,100
Should we get them some Chinese medicine? 

135
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:23,760
Don't feed her. 

136
00:07:23,760 --> 00:07:27,020
When my kids complain,
I take the food away. 

137
00:07:27,020 --> 00:07:28,730
I let them go hungry and got rid of snacks. 

138
00:07:28,730 --> 00:07:30,940
Now they eat everything I give them. 

139
00:07:30,940 --> 00:07:33,190
She's not like your kids! 

140
00:07:33,190 --> 00:07:35,800
She's different from poor kids. 

141
00:07:40,130 --> 00:07:42,350
Sit back down.
I have the perfect solution. 

142
00:07:42,350 --> 00:07:43,460
It works every time. 

143
00:07:53,750 --> 00:07:55,740
- Yes, Subak?
- Hurry, hurry. 

144
00:07:56,910 --> 00:08:00,150
- I can't. I'm outside.
- She's crying! 

145
00:08:00,150 --> 00:08:01,820
Oh, man. 

146
00:08:01,820 --> 00:08:02,870
Hold on. 

147
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:25,900
See? It worked. 

148
00:08:25,900 --> 00:08:27,870
Gwangbak's barking put her right to sleep. 

149
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:30,940
I was wondering what that sound was about. 

150
00:08:30,940 --> 00:08:33,470
Anyway, Gwangbak's been giving me insomnia. 

151
00:08:33,470 --> 00:08:35,550
Let her be.
She can take care of herself. 

152
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:39,570
This month's allowance. 

153
00:08:40,280 --> 00:08:42,230
You're the best. 

154
00:08:43,070 --> 00:08:46,510
My precious, precious daughter. 

155
00:08:47,780 --> 00:08:49,080
Dinner's ready. 

156
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:50,890
Thank you. 

157
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:53,560
I'm going.
Mom, you're staying, right? 

158
00:08:53,560 --> 00:08:56,040
I should prepare dinner for Minjung. 

159
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:58,210
Hobak, over there. 

160
00:09:01,170 --> 00:09:04,760
You never help her out for free. 

161
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:06,740
You must've gotten rich off her! 

162
00:09:08,090 --> 00:09:11,780
I have a money room.
It reeks of money. 

163
00:09:11,780 --> 00:09:13,480
You know how great that smells? 

164
00:09:14,510 --> 00:09:17,990
If you have clothes you don't wear,
can I have them? 

165
00:09:17,990 --> 00:09:20,320
But you never wear anything I give you. 

166
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:21,820
And you don't carry the bags I give you. 

167
00:09:21,820 --> 00:09:23,910
I wear them when I go to work. 

168
00:09:23,910 --> 00:09:26,120
Give me everything you don't need. 

169
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:28,320
You don't even look good in them. 

170
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:31,090
I'd take them if I could wear them. 

171
00:09:31,090 --> 00:09:34,490
Subak, you looked great in anything. 

172
00:09:34,490 --> 00:09:36,090
And Hobak looked awkward in everything. 

173
00:09:36,090 --> 00:09:38,580
You were Chunhyang, and she was Hyangdan. 

174
00:09:41,730 --> 00:09:45,520
Why don't you quit your job and work here? 

175
00:09:46,380 --> 00:09:48,540
- Huh?
- I pay you well. 

176
00:09:48,540 --> 00:09:50,350
Quit that dumb job. 

177
00:09:51,370 --> 00:09:53,470
It's not dumb. 

178
00:09:53,470 --> 00:09:55,630
That's a great idea. 

179
00:09:55,630 --> 00:09:57,390
Quit your job and work at your sister's. 

180
00:09:57,390 --> 00:09:58,820
I'd do it in a heartbeat. 

181
00:10:12,890 --> 00:10:14,080
Minjung. 

182
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:18,010
- You came for a visit?
- Yes. 

183
00:10:19,500 --> 00:10:20,700
Where's your car? 

184
00:10:22,550 --> 00:10:23,890
It's at the shop. 

185
00:10:23,890 --> 00:10:25,340
You haven't had dinner, have you? 

186
00:10:25,340 --> 00:10:27,180
I made zucchini soybean paste stew. 

187
00:10:28,350 --> 00:10:30,470
Is something wrong? 

188
00:10:30,470 --> 00:10:32,470
No. Why? 

189
00:10:32,470 --> 00:10:38,140
You fired the housekeeper out of the blue,
and you don't look very happy. 

190
00:10:38,140 --> 00:10:41,020
I'm just tired.
I'll see you again. 

191
00:10:41,020 --> 00:10:43,360
Yes, Minjung. Take care. 

192
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:48,020
Hobak. 

193
00:10:49,130 --> 00:10:50,400
Yes? 

194
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:55,640
What is it? 

195
00:10:55,640 --> 00:10:57,620
Do you have something to tell me? 

196
00:10:58,620 --> 00:11:01,130
Uh, no. Maybe later. 

197
00:11:01,130 --> 00:11:02,270
Bye. 

198
00:11:15,880 --> 00:11:16,910
I can eat by myself. 

199
00:11:16,910 --> 00:11:19,830
It's okay. I want to do this. 

200
00:11:22,230 --> 00:11:26,230
And Minjung, be honest with me. 

201
00:11:27,870 --> 00:11:30,620
Why did you fire the housekeeper? 

202
00:11:30,620 --> 00:11:34,080
Are you trying to teach Subak a lesson? 

203
00:11:34,970 --> 00:11:37,950
She should run the house and raise the kids. 

204
00:11:38,710 --> 00:11:42,040
But she doesn't know how to do anything. 

205
00:11:42,040 --> 00:11:45,240
She never washed so much as one pair of undies herself. 

206
00:11:46,130 --> 00:11:50,410
You know how I raised her like a princess. 

207
00:11:50,410 --> 00:11:52,170
She was even in the Miss Korea pageant. 

208
00:11:53,390 --> 00:11:55,600
But she's a mom with two daughters. 

209
00:11:55,600 --> 00:11:57,600
She should be able to do anything. 

210
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:59,600
Are you having an affair? 

211
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:01,860
Of course not. 

212
00:12:01,860 --> 00:12:02,860
No. Right? 

213
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:06,230
You won't find a woman like Subak anywhere. 

214
00:12:06,230 --> 00:12:08,230
Go look. 

215
00:12:08,230 --> 00:12:09,840
She's pretty and lovely. 

216
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:12,570
What else would you need in a woman? 

217
00:12:14,670 --> 00:12:16,660
What is it?
Did it go down the wrong way? 

218
00:12:16,660 --> 00:12:20,030
Drink some water, here, here, here. 

219
00:12:20,780 --> 00:12:22,510
More, more, more, 

220
00:12:28,010 --> 00:12:30,650
Mom, should I get a face lift, like this? 

221
00:12:30,650 --> 00:12:32,160
I look 10 years younger, don't I? 

222
00:12:32,160 --> 00:12:33,910
You already look young. 

223
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:38,480
I asked and there's no other woman. 

224
00:12:39,580 --> 00:12:40,480
No? 

225
00:12:41,780 --> 00:12:44,090
All my friends husbands have girlfriends. 

226
00:12:44,090 --> 00:12:45,480
Be nice to him. 

227
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:48,590
Where would you find another man like him? 

228
00:12:48,590 --> 00:12:51,210
He's handsome, rich, good tempered. 

229
00:12:51,210 --> 00:12:53,390
If he were available, women would line up. 

230
00:12:53,390 --> 00:12:56,200
But where would he find a woman like me? 

231
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:58,260
Everyone thinks I'm younger than my age. 

232
00:12:58,950 --> 00:13:00,530
Mom, would you like to get a face lift? 

233
00:13:01,180 --> 00:13:03,960
I would love to. 

234
00:13:06,670 --> 00:13:09,110
Oh, my, it looks so nice. 

235
00:13:09,110 --> 00:13:10,300
Right? 

236
00:13:11,170 --> 00:13:14,820
Oh, what the hell?
Should I just get it? 

237
00:13:15,700 --> 00:13:17,700
What could your father do after it's done? 

238
00:13:17,700 --> 00:13:19,360
He can't un-lift it, right? 

239
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:22,410
Right. Just go for it.
Who cares? 

240
00:13:27,160 --> 00:13:28,190
Here. 

241
00:13:28,190 --> 00:13:31,530
Oh, my! These are all luxury brands! 

242
00:13:31,530 --> 00:13:33,020
They are in great condition! 

243
00:13:33,020 --> 00:13:35,250
Hobak, where did you get these? 

244
00:13:36,270 --> 00:13:38,370
Pick what you want.
Aren't they pretty? 

245
00:13:38,370 --> 00:13:39,490
Give me a good deal on this. 

246
00:13:39,490 --> 00:13:40,620
Don't worry,
I will give you a great deal. 

247
00:13:40,620 --> 00:13:42,540
Hey, this would look great on you. 

248
00:13:44,590 --> 00:13:45,830
$100. 

249
00:13:45,830 --> 00:13:47,020
Yes! 

250
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:50,390
$100. Okay. 

251
00:14:07,820 --> 00:14:09,220
Mom. 

252
00:14:09,220 --> 00:14:12,140
A big hair salon is opening down the street. 

253
00:14:14,450 --> 00:14:17,260
Thinking about that is making me so angry. 

254
00:14:17,260 --> 00:14:21,140
What can I do with such a tiny shop? 

255
00:14:21,140 --> 00:14:23,660
Why can't you find a rich man? 

256
00:14:23,660 --> 00:14:25,570
I don't know what you do when you go out. 

257
00:14:25,570 --> 00:14:27,750
What do you think I'm doing? 

258
00:14:27,750 --> 00:14:31,710
I've been looking for a rich, handsome man who would love me and nobody else. 

259
00:14:31,710 --> 00:14:35,000
Don't just meet anyone.
Find the right one. 

260
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:36,730
Look at the vice principal's daughter Subak. 

261
00:14:36,730 --> 00:14:38,650
That's how you become a good daughter. 

262
00:14:38,650 --> 00:14:39,950
Just wait. 

263
00:14:39,950 --> 00:14:42,520
Don't compare me to her. 

264
00:14:42,520 --> 00:14:45,290
Oh, ask Hobak to lend you money. 

265
00:14:45,290 --> 00:14:47,170
She's always saving money. 

266
00:14:47,170 --> 00:14:48,880
I'm sure she has some tucked away. 

267
00:14:56,440 --> 00:14:58,040
Why didn't you come in? 

268
00:14:58,040 --> 00:14:59,340
I missed you, uncle. 

269
