Life is long, so missing a few days of school isn't a big deal. 

542
00:31:06,640 --> 00:31:11,920
What we should do is wait for Daebak to find his dream and decide to go back to school. 

543
00:31:11,920 --> 00:31:13,900
Wait? Why should we? 

544
00:31:13,900 --> 00:31:15,690
We should be him up, if it comes to that. 

545
00:31:19,430 --> 00:31:23,240
What you said, all three of them, are right. 

546
00:31:24,110 --> 00:31:25,790
So what do you want to do? 

547
00:31:25,790 --> 00:31:26,770
Leave him be. 

548
00:31:26,770 --> 00:31:28,500
Leave him be like that? 

549
00:31:28,500 --> 00:31:32,210
Let's pretend we left him on an island. 

550
00:31:32,210 --> 00:31:36,190
He's a middle school boy, extremely wild. 

551
00:31:36,190 --> 00:31:39,520
This is what I tell the teachers. 

552
00:31:39,520 --> 00:31:45,620
Everyone's born with a certain amount of wildness in his blood, 

553
00:31:45,620 --> 00:31:50,160
and if he doesn't act it out when he's young, he'll do it... 

554
00:31:50,160 --> 00:31:51,260
What's he talking about? 

555
00:31:51,260 --> 00:31:55,260
If you're going to go wild, do it early. 

556
00:31:55,260 --> 00:31:56,800
Mom, you're smart. 

557
00:31:56,800 --> 00:32:00,110
Mother understands, so why can't you? 

558
00:32:00,110 --> 00:32:01,900
Because we're of different blood. 

559
00:32:01,900 --> 00:32:08,450
Cheating on your spouse when you're old is dangerous,
so do it when you're young. 

560
00:32:08,450 --> 00:32:09,380
Don't you think so? 

561
00:32:09,380 --> 00:32:11,810
That's not it, grandma. 

562
00:32:15,890 --> 00:32:17,430
Did they call? 

563
00:32:18,960 --> 00:32:21,650
They said they would,
but they haven't yet. 

564
00:32:24,840 --> 00:32:26,830
How do you feel? 

565
00:32:26,830 --> 00:32:31,000
I'm nervous. I don't know. 

566
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:33,080
I don't know what I'd say when I see her. 

567
00:32:34,270 --> 00:32:36,910
You didn't get a call did you? 

568
00:32:36,910 --> 00:32:38,060
No. 

569
00:32:39,240 --> 00:32:42,100
How can she be so heartless? 

570
00:32:42,100 --> 00:32:44,100
Doesn't she miss you? 

571
00:32:48,150 --> 00:32:49,360
Sangnam, 

572
00:32:50,530 --> 00:32:52,930
if you can't forgive her, 

573
00:32:52,930 --> 00:32:55,140
don't meet her. 

574
00:32:55,140 --> 00:32:58,860
I'm worried you might get hurt. 

575
00:32:59,480 --> 00:33:01,100
I'm already hurt. 

576
00:33:03,010 --> 00:33:05,000
I thought it had healed... 

577
00:33:07,920 --> 00:33:10,570
Even if I get hurt again, 

578
00:33:10,570 --> 00:33:12,570
I have to meet her. 

579
00:33:14,100 --> 00:33:15,770
Only then can I get over it. 

580
00:33:17,580 --> 00:33:19,940
I don't know what to say. 

581
00:33:21,470 --> 00:33:22,940
I'm sorry. 

582
00:33:22,940 --> 00:33:24,720
Why would you be sorry? 

583
00:33:24,720 --> 00:33:25,930
Don't be. 

584
00:33:29,300 --> 00:33:31,500
Don't get mad and go to sleep. 

585
00:33:31,500 --> 00:33:33,110
How can I not get mad? 

586
00:33:33,110 --> 00:33:36,860
Whom did our kids take after? 

587
00:33:37,640 --> 00:33:41,960
They took after their parents.
Go to sleep. 

588
00:33:41,960 --> 00:33:43,910
A middle school drop out!
How awful! 

589
00:33:43,910 --> 00:33:46,830
And his father's a vice principal! Ugh... 

590
00:33:59,900 --> 00:34:03,200
Everyone go inside.
Daebak, follow me. 

591
00:34:06,320 --> 00:34:08,690
You're dead! 

592
00:34:48,830 --> 00:34:50,190
Daebak, 

593
00:34:52,330 --> 00:34:54,490
you don't want to go to school? 

594
00:34:57,260 --> 00:34:58,770
I don't want to go to school, either. 

595
00:35:00,740 --> 00:35:03,310
The Board of Education's breathing down my neck. 

596
00:35:03,310 --> 00:35:07,380
I've go so much to do,
but teachers won't listen to me, 

597
00:35:07,380 --> 00:35:10,180
the principal is out to get me, 

598
00:35:10,180 --> 00:35:12,570
and the students call me the "geezer." 

599
00:35:13,870 --> 00:35:20,360
I want to quit, but I can't because I won't be able to support you guys. 

600
00:35:22,530 --> 00:35:23,920
Oh... 

601
00:35:45,190 --> 00:35:46,480
Be frugal. 

602
00:35:46,930 --> 00:35:50,280
What's there to save?
It's $3. 

603
00:35:50,280 --> 00:35:51,760
If you don't want it, forget it. 

604
00:35:54,020 --> 00:35:57,460
Even beef soup is 7 or 8 dollars. 

605
00:35:57,460 --> 00:36:00,300
Don't eat out!
There's food here. 

606
00:36:00,300 --> 00:36:03,190
For a man, his wallet gives him self esteem. 

607
00:36:03,190 --> 00:36:06,920
My self esteem is worth $3. 

608
00:36:06,920 --> 00:36:09,910
Then go make money.
You're healthy enough. 

609
00:36:09,910 --> 00:36:12,240
- Get up!
- Hey! 

610
00:36:14,060 --> 00:36:16,980
Go to bed early and stop playing computer games all night! 

611
00:36:17,560 --> 00:36:20,250
It gets rid of bad odor. 

612
00:36:20,250 --> 00:36:22,230
You mean idle thoughts. 

613
00:36:22,230 --> 00:36:25,070
- Stop talking nonsense and get up!
- Man! 

614
00:36:25,070 --> 00:36:29,200
All you think of when you're awake is this? 

615
00:36:29,200 --> 00:36:32,510
I think of it when I'm asleep. 

616
00:36:35,140 --> 00:36:37,910
- Get up right now!
- Man! Give it back! 

617
00:36:47,140 --> 00:36:48,790
I'm going to school. 

618
00:36:50,320 --> 00:36:52,810
Standing together like this is awkward. 

619
00:36:52,810 --> 00:36:54,280
Watch out for cars! 

620
00:36:54,280 --> 00:36:57,870
Cross the street when the light's green! 

621
00:36:57,870 --> 00:37:00,920
He's only going to school. Big deal! 

622
00:37:00,920 --> 00:37:04,790
Uncle, don't you want to go to work? 

623
00:37:05,610 --> 00:37:07,920
Ya, hyo, hyo, hyo, hyo. 

624
00:37:08,960 --> 00:37:11,250
Wang Daebak, go for it! 

625
00:37:32,720 --> 00:37:36,530
Hello? I'm Daebak's sister, Gwangbak. 

626
00:37:37,350 --> 00:37:39,290
Not Pibak, Gwangbak. 

627
00:37:39,290 --> 00:37:40,720
Hello? 

628
00:37:42,320 --> 00:37:44,550
I can't here you. Who is it? 

629
00:37:44,550 --> 00:37:49,310
Gwangbak. Daebak's sister, Gwangbak. 

630
00:37:49,310 --> 00:37:50,750
Oh... 

631
00:37:50,750 --> 00:37:53,030
What's up? I'm busy. 

632
00:37:53,030 --> 00:37:55,080
Since you're busy, I'll make it short. 

633
00:37:55,080 --> 00:37:59,060
Daebak went to school today, finally. 

634
00:37:59,060 --> 00:38:00,550
It was quite moving. 

635
00:38:00,550 --> 00:38:02,080
Thank you so much. 

636
00:38:02,080 --> 00:38:03,250
So I was thinking... 

637
00:38:03,250 --> 00:38:04,680
Get to the point. 

638
00:38:04,680 --> 00:38:06,580
Yes, yes. I'll get to the point. 

639
00:38:06,580 --> 00:38:08,960
I want to buy you dinner, to thank you. 

640
00:38:08,960 --> 00:38:10,890
You don't have to. 

641
00:38:10,890 --> 00:38:15,340
But if you're asking me out on a date, sure why not? 

642
00:38:15,340 --> 00:38:17,270
Let's make it tonight, then. 

643
00:38:17,270 --> 00:38:19,140
Let's meet when I get off from work,  

644
00:38:19,140 --> 00:38:20,460
and can I decide where? 

645
00:38:20,460 --> 00:38:22,450
Sure, sure. Whatever you want. 

646
00:38:22,450 --> 00:38:24,940
I'll see you at the construction site. 

647
00:38:25,370 --> 00:38:26,220
Yes! 

648
00:38:32,620 --> 00:38:33,930
I'm worried. 

649
00:38:33,930 --> 00:38:37,800
You might quit your job after we're married. 

650
00:38:37,800 --> 00:38:39,800
You dropped out of school just like that. 

651
00:38:39,800 --> 00:38:41,370
A job is different. 

652
00:38:41,370 --> 00:38:45,070
I'm not going to get a job. 

653
00:38:45,070 --> 00:38:46,800
I'm going to become a housewife. 

654
00:38:46,800 --> 00:38:48,810
These days, we need to be a dual income family. 

655
00:38:48,810 --> 00:38:50,930
We can't survive on a single income. 

656
00:38:50,930 --> 00:38:56,850
There are so many vice principals who can't quit because of their families. 

657
00:38:57,590 --> 00:38:59,710
I will be frugal. 

658
00:38:59,710 --> 00:39:03,240
Daebak, you're not a mama's boy, are you? 

659
00:39:04,660 --> 00:39:06,650
How can you even ask? 

660
00:39:07,170 --> 00:39:08,640
Daebak! 

661
00:39:10,130 --> 00:39:11,120
Oh, hey. 

662
00:39:15,470 --> 00:39:16,730
Who was that? 

663
00:39:16,730 --> 00:39:18,280
My class vice president. 

664
00:39:20,250 --> 00:39:21,700
Pretty, huh? 

665
00:39:21,700 --> 00:39:23,650
She's not pretty! 

666
00:39:23,650 --> 00:39:24,930
You don't know what you're talking about. 

667
00:39:29,240 --> 00:39:30,520
Stop that. 

668
00:39:31,900 --> 00:39:34,220
Daebak, what are you doing? 

669
00:39:35,540 --> 00:39:37,090
Daebak! 

670
00:39:37,090 --> 00:39:39,450
Why? What is it? 

671
00:39:45,030 --> 00:39:47,020
Daebak, stop right there! 

672
00:39:54,690 --> 00:39:56,450
Men are so immature. 

673
00:39:56,920 --> 00:39:58,260
They are all cheaters. 

674
00:39:58,700 --> 00:40:00,680
Is Daebak cheating on you? 

675
00:40:00,680 --> 00:40:03,170
He keeps looking at other women. 

676
00:40:03,170 --> 00:40:06,960
Who cares.
You're prettier than any of them. 

677
00:40:07,880 --> 00:40:11,150
I know that, but it still feels bad. 

678
00:40:11,840 --> 00:40:15,260
Mom, do you think I should marry him? 

679
00:40:15,260 --> 00:40:18,800
He has 4 sisters and his mom's scary. 

680
00:40:18,800 --> 00:40:20,800
You're scared of his mom already? 

681
00:40:20,800 --> 00:40:22,980
In laws are always intimidating. 

682
00:40:22,980 --> 00:40:25,820
I just need to win over his third sister. 

683
00:40:25,820 --> 00:40:26,820
Why? 

684
00:40:26,820 --> 00:40:28,820
She's really difficult. 

685
00:40:28,820 --> 00:40:31,760
Even his parents can't handle her. 

686
00:40:31,760 --> 00:40:33,760
Do you have any ideas? 

687
00:40:33,760 --> 00:40:35,910
I don't know. 

688
00:40:35,910 --> 00:40:38,650
Why do you speak with an accent with Daebak? 

689
00:40:38,650 --> 00:40:40,320
You can speak without it fine. 

690
00:40:40,320 --> 00:40:45,360
Seoul men love girls from Gyeongsang-do Province. 

691
00:40:45,360 --> 00:40:49,010
When I go, Daebak, he melts away. 

692
00:40:49,480 --> 00:40:51,080
Oh, boy. 

693
00:40:51,080 --> 00:40:54,350
Who's daughter are you?
How precious! 

694
00:40:54,350 --> 00:40:56,750
Yours, of course. 

695
00:41:20,450 --> 00:41:22,310
- Let's go.
- Huh? 

696
00:41:27,200 --> 00:41:30,050
Why did you get all dressed up? 

697
00:41:30,050 --> 00:41:31,320
I'm not dressed up. 

698
00:41:33,790 --> 00:41:36,040
You want to look nice to someone? 

699
00:41:36,040 --> 00:41:38,020
No, it's not that. 

700
00:41:42,440 --> 00:41:44,700
Oh, my! Oh, my! 

701
00:41:44,700 --> 00:41:48,410
I was going to help you.
Are you nervous? 

702
00:41:48,410 --> 00:41:50,270
No, I'm not nervous. 

703
00:41:50,270 --> 00:41:52,690
So you're not nervous. 

704
00:41:52,690 --> 00:41:56,120
When you get nervous, you get chatty. 

705
00:42:08,710 --> 00:42:09,810
Thank you. 

706
00:42:16,170 --> 00:42:17,660
Let's eat. 

707
00:42:22,680 --> 00:42:24,210
Why? What's wrong? 

708
00:42:26,960 --> 00:42:28,910
Why? What is it? 

709
00:42:29,640 --> 00:42:31,180
It's so delicious. 

710
00:42:32,520 --> 00:42:35,780
It looks bad, but it tastes amazing. Try it. 

711
00:42:41,490 --> 00:42:42,790
It's good. 

712
00:42:42,790 --> 00:42:44,210
You must come here often. 

713
00:42:44,210 --> 00:42:45,490
I have a name. 

714
00:42:45,490 --> 00:42:46,890
It's Choi Sangnam. 

715
00:42:47,650 --> 00:42:52,710
My dad named me Sangnam,
"the man of men", so I can become the best. 

716
00:42:52,710 --> 00:42:55,540
Gwangbak's a Go-Stop term, isn't it? 

717
00:42:55,540 --> 00:42:56,860
Your parents must like the game. 

718
00:42:56,860 --> 00:43:00,260
No, and I hope I don't have a bad hand in life. 

719
00:43:00,260 --> 00:43:01,990
I hope I have a good hand. 

720
00:43:02,850 --> 00:43:04,490
Did you know? 

721
00:43:04,490 --> 00:43:07,220
You can't win with too many good cards. 

722
00:43:08,260 --> 00:43:12,300
If you have everything, you can't succeed. 

723
00:43:12,300 --> 00:43:16,370
You only work hard when you lack something. 

724
00:43:16,370 --> 00:43:21,040
Most successful people got there after overcoming their shortcomings. 

725
00:43:21,040 --> 00:43:23,040
My grandmother said something similar. 

726
00:43:23,040 --> 00:43:26,140
When you have a few good cards, you win. 

727
00:43:26,850 --> 00:43:30,160
So I think you have a good hand in life. 

728
00:43:30,160 --> 00:43:32,000
Because you seem to have many shortcomings. 

729
00:43:32,000 --> 00:43:33,860
Should I lest them? 

730
00:43:33,860 --> 00:43:35,820
First, you're ugly. 

731
00:43:35,820 --> 00:43:37,280
No way. 

732
00:43:39,740 --> 00:43:42,330
- Hot!
- You're impatient. 

733
00:43:42,330 --> 00:43:45,450
You have to blow on it before you eat it. 

734
00:43:46,070 --> 00:43:46,940
Get some, like this. 

735
00:43:51,350 --> 00:43:52,390
Okay. 

736
00:43:52,750 --> 00:43:54,390
You have a foul mouth. 

737
00:43:54,390 --> 00:43:55,440
But I don't! 

738
00:43:55,440 --> 00:43:57,690
I heard you on Daebak's phone. 

739
00:43:57,690 --> 00:44:00,560
Wow, I can't even remember what you said. 

740
00:44:00,560 --> 00:44:01,800
- That's...
- Shh! 

741
00:44:02,490 --> 00:44:04,560
So out a five card hand, 

742
00:44:04,560 --> 00:44:08,020
you're ugly, impatient and foul mouthed. 

743
00:44:08,020 --> 00:44:10,400
That's three useless cards. 

744
00:44:10,400 --> 00:44:12,400
I'll count the rest as good cards. 

745
00:44:12,400 --> 00:44:15,580
Let's find out what those two cards are. 

746
00:44:17,430 --> 00:44:19,810
You should be getting a call by now. 

747
00:44:29,540 --> 00:44:30,980
You're so funny. 

748
00:44:30,980 --> 00:44:33,250
- Me?
- Yes. 

749
00:44:33,250 --> 00:44:35,110
That hasn't helped me. 

750
00:44:35,110 --> 00:44:36,950
Women are so weird. 

751
00:44:36,950 --> 00:44:41,870
I make them laugh, but they always run to the men who make them cry. 

752
00:44:42,750 --> 00:44:44,430
How do you know when so well? 

753
00:44:44,430 --> 00:44:45,920
I'm a player. 

754
00:44:45,920 --> 00:44:49,690
No real player says he's a player. 

755
00:44:49,690 --> 00:44:51,290
But it's true. 

756
00:44:56,970 --> 00:44:59,310
Let me give you a tip. 

757
00:44:59,310 --> 00:45:02,100
Don't fall for me. 

758
00:45:02,100 --> 00:45:04,760
I hate it when women cry. 

759
00:45:18,530 --> 00:45:25,300
This isn't much of a grand opening,
but we'll have a great party later. 

760
00:45:25,300 --> 00:45:29,300
Let's put our hearts together and work hard. 

761
00:45:29,300 --> 00:45:31,630
But Mr. Ko, 

762
00:45:31,630 --> 00:45:33,850
you've never done this kind of work before. 

763
00:45:35,270 --> 00:45:38,860
I helped my friend do this a long time ago. 

764
00:45:40,710 --> 00:45:43,740
I'll deliver to the difficult places. 

765
00:45:43,740 --> 00:45:45,340
So please help me. 

766
00:45:45,340 --> 00:45:46,320
Yes, sir! 

767
00:45:46,320 --> 00:45:49,240
For Minjung Parcel service.

768
00:45:49,240 --> 00:45:50,250
Cheers! 

769
00:45:50,250 --> 00:45:52,610
Next Saturday's mom's 60th birthday. 

770
00:45:52,610 --> 00:45:55,900
Let's have dinner and send her on a trip. 

771
00:45:55,900 --> 00:45:57,640
Where to?
Jeju-do Island? 

772
00:45:57,640 --> 00:46:00,740
Mom's been saying she wants to go on a cruise. 

773
00:46:00,740 --> 00:46:03,050
Expensive.
Where are we having dinner? 

774
00:46:03,050 --> 00:46:06,380
At a hotel.
Either a buffet or a steakhouse. 

775
00:46:07,160 --> 00:46:08,790
That'll be expensive. 

776
00:46:08,790 --> 00:46:12,820
It's $100 to $300 per person. 

777
00:46:14,550 --> 00:46:18,390
Let's invite some guests.
Is 100 guests okay? 

778
00:46:18,390 --> 00:46:21,040
100 guests?
How much is that? 

779
00:46:21,040 --> 00:46:23,140
I can't do that.
That's too much. 

780
00:46:23,140 --> 00:46:25,140
Right. And I'm unemployed. 

781
00:46:25,140 --> 00:46:27,440
How can you bring up money? 

782
00:46:27,440 --> 00:46:30,120
Mom will turn 60 only once! 

783
00:46:30,120 --> 00:46:32,670
You stay out of it then. I'll take care of it. 

784
00:46:32,670 --> 00:46:34,440
Haebak, are you okay with this? 

785
00:46:53,560 --> 00:46:55,750
- Hello?
- Hey, I'm disappointed in you. 

786
00:46:57,080 --> 00:46:58,170
Mom. 

787
00:46:58,170 --> 00:47:02,140
How can you be so selfish?
You make money! 

788
00:47:02,140 --> 00:47:04,780
You want to cancel my 60th birthday party? 

789
00:47:04,780 --> 00:47:06,250
It's not that. 

790
00:47:06,250 --> 00:47:10,010
Subak's suggestion is way out of my budget. 

791
00:47:10,010 --> 00:47:13,130
You've never bought me anything. 

792
00:47:13,130 --> 00:47:15,380
Your husband never gave me any allowance. 

793
00:47:15,380 --> 00:47:17,610
This is how people are. 

794
00:47:17,610 --> 00:47:19,830
When you get something, you give. 

795
00:47:19,830 --> 00:47:22,530
And I'm not asking for something big. 

796
00:47:22,530 --> 00:47:28,220
I know I have no excuse for that,
but you know how I live. 

797
00:47:28,220 --> 00:47:31,490
Sedal won't help and my kids are growing, 

798
00:47:31,490 --> 00:47:33,280
so I've been trying so hard to save every penny... 

799
00:47:33,280 --> 00:47:34,540
Whatever! 

800
00:47:36,260 --> 00:47:38,710
Mom, mom! 

801
00:47:50,470 --> 00:47:53,170
How could you! How? 

802
00:47:53,170 --> 00:47:55,600
Are you boy crazy? 

803
00:47:56,160 --> 00:47:58,540
Why couldn't you get a job and help me out? 

804
00:47:58,540 --> 00:48:01,830
Your older sister isn't even married yet! 

805
00:48:02,510 --> 00:48:06,690
They'll think there's something wrong with her for you to get married first. 

806
00:48:07,380 --> 00:48:10,060
What if this ruins Subak's chances of marrying? 

807
00:48:10,060 --> 00:48:11,810
Do whatever you want! 

808
00:48:11,810 --> 00:48:17,070
I'm not going to think of you as my daughter! 

809
00:48:17,070 --> 00:48:20,150
Ugh! How could anyone love you? 

810
00:48:38,860 --> 00:48:41,400
Oh, hold the elevator! 

811
00:48:44,590 --> 00:48:45,970
Oh, hi. 

812
00:48:45,970 --> 00:48:48,740
I got a call about a special article. 

813
00:48:48,740 --> 00:48:50,930
Wasn't someone else doing it? 

814
00:48:50,930 --> 00:48:53,850
She had to quit because something came up. 

815
00:48:53,850 --> 00:48:57,410
The deadline's close.
Can you handle it? 

816
00:48:57,410 --> 00:49:00,010
I'll do it.
What's it about? 

817
00:49:00,010 --> 00:49:02,750
The field everyone woman is interested in. 

818
00:49:02,750 --> 00:49:04,420
Men's job world. 

819
00:49:04,420 --> 00:49:06,630
That sounds interesting. 

820
00:49:06,630 --> 00:49:08,490
Types of jobs that are popular. 

821
00:49:08,490 --> 00:49:11,210
Talk about which jobs will become hot, 

822
00:49:11,210 --> 00:49:13,240
which job fields single women prefer. 

823
00:49:13,240 --> 00:49:16,090
I want a series of articles on that. 

824
00:49:16,090 --> 00:49:17,890
You can figure out the rest. 

825
00:49:17,890 --> 00:49:19,400
You've done it before, right? 

826
00:49:28,480 --> 00:49:30,350
[Arrogant Bulldozer] 

827
00:49:33,870 --> 00:49:36,980
This is Gwangbak.
I need to talk to you. 

828
00:49:36,980 --> 00:49:38,780
Then let's do it face to face. 

829
00:49:38,780 --> 00:49:40,400
We live in the same neighborhood anyway. 

830
00:49:40,400 --> 00:49:42,620
I'll see you at the playground. 

831
00:49:42,620 --> 00:49:44,030
Hello? 

832
00:50:21,350 --> 00:50:23,930
You got into an accident again? 

833
00:50:23,930 --> 00:50:25,520
What is it? 

834
00:50:25,520 --> 00:50:27,300
I want to interview you. 

835
00:50:27,300 --> 00:50:28,570
Interrogation? 

836
00:50:28,570 --> 00:50:30,730
I like it when women interrogate me. 

837
00:50:30,730 --> 00:50:32,120
Mmm... Player. 

838
00:50:32,120 --> 00:50:33,760
I told you I was. 

839
00:50:33,760 --> 00:50:36,200
This time, it's just an interview. 

840
00:50:36,200 --> 00:50:39,390
It's a magazine article on men's jobs. 

841
00:50:39,390 --> 00:50:41,700
A-ha! I got it. 

842
00:50:41,700 --> 00:50:44,160
You should come to the construction site. 

843
00:50:44,160 --> 00:50:46,590
Is that okay?
It'll be dusty and noisy. 

844
00:50:46,590 --> 00:50:48,810
Fine. I'll be taking pictures. 

845
00:50:48,810 --> 00:50:51,990
Good. Your magazine will sell like crazy. 

846
00:50:51,990 --> 00:50:53,560
Pick a time and call me. 

847
00:51:03,730 --> 00:51:05,010
Are you going on a blind date? 

848
00:51:05,010 --> 00:51:05,890
Excuse me? 

849
00:51:05,890 --> 00:51:09,240
Did you get all dressed up to meet me at the playground? 

850
00:51:09,240 --> 00:51:11,690
Good luck on your blind date! 

851
00:51:14,130 --> 00:51:15,780
How arrogant. 

852
00:51:29,400 --> 00:51:30,740
It's me, Choi Sangnam. 

853
00:51:32,570 --> 00:51:33,700
Are you certain? 

854
00:51:36,100 --> 00:51:37,870
Okay. I'll be right over. 

855
00:51:55,040 --> 00:51:56,620
I'm going. 

856
00:51:56,620 --> 00:51:57,940
Sangnam. 

857
00:51:59,860 --> 00:52:03,160
I'm nervous.
I don't know what to say. 

858
00:52:03,470 --> 00:52:05,140
Do and say whatever you want. 

859
00:52:05,140 --> 00:52:09,600
Do everything you want.
You have the right. 

860
00:52:11,240 --> 00:52:12,900
Auntie, I'll see you later. 

861
00:52:12,900 --> 00:52:15,240
- You didn't go to work?
- I already did. 

862
00:52:19,820 --> 00:52:21,850
Where's he going?
All dressed up? 

863
00:52:21,850 --> 00:52:23,880
He's meeting his friends. 

864
00:52:47,000 --> 00:52:49,980
$3? Down there is $2. 

865
00:52:49,980 --> 00:52:53,050
You know how expensive things are! 

866
00:52:53,050 --> 00:52:55,950
I left it at the front desk like you asked. 

867
00:52:57,160 --> 00:53:00,880
No, not there, the main front desk. 

868
00:53:02,220 --> 00:53:04,220
[Minjung Parcel Service] 

869
00:53:24,100 --> 00:53:25,250
Mom, what is it? 

870
00:53:25,250 --> 00:53:27,250
Is everything okay at home? 

871
00:53:27,250 --> 00:53:28,530
Of course. What is it? 

872
00:53:28,530 --> 00:53:30,340
I saw something weird today. 

873
00:53:31,580 --> 00:53:32,430
Why? What was it? 

874
00:53:32,430 --> 00:53:34,430
Is Minjung's company doing okay? 

875
00:53:34,430 --> 00:53:36,430
Of course! 

876
00:53:36,430 --> 00:53:37,940
And he didn't say anything? 

877
00:53:37,940 --> 00:53:39,590
Why? What is it? 

878
00:53:39,590 --> 00:53:43,500
It's nothing. I'm old.
I'm seeing things. 

879
00:53:44,100 --> 00:53:45,830
He could've been his twin. 

880
00:53:45,830 --> 00:53:48,390
- Who?
- Nothing. I'll talk to you later. 

881
00:53:48,390 --> 00:53:51,630
Mom, can you get my kids? 

882
00:53:51,630 --> 00:53:54,030
I left them with the lady on the first floor. I'll be home late. 

883
00:53:54,030 --> 00:53:55,320
Okay. 

884
00:53:56,580 --> 00:54:00,060
I knew it.
That scared me good. 

885
00:54:00,060 --> 00:54:02,460
How could he look so much like him? 

886
00:54:12,390 --> 00:54:14,250
Oh, boy. 

887
00:54:14,250 --> 00:54:17,010
I looked, but I couldn't find any jobs. 

888
00:54:17,010 --> 00:54:19,150
I really want to sign a contract. 

889
00:54:19,150 --> 00:54:21,810
You were too busy playing games. 

890
00:54:21,810 --> 00:54:24,730
No, I really want to find a job. 

891
00:54:26,720 --> 00:54:28,510
Big sis, 

892
00:54:28,510 --> 00:54:30,090
let's eat out. 

893
00:54:31,070 --> 00:54:34,350
Go home and eat.
I already cooked rice. 

894
00:54:40,020 --> 00:54:46,090
Sedal, we'll have to pitch in for my mom's party. 

895
00:54:47,670 --> 00:54:48,650
What? 

896
00:55:10,570 --> 00:55:12,840
This is nuts! 

897
00:55:13,100 --> 00:55:15,180
Hotel buffet and a cruise? 

898
00:55:15,180 --> 00:55:18,350
You tell your rich sister to pay for them. 

899
00:55:18,350 --> 00:55:21,160
$1,000 or $2,000 means nothing to them. 

900
00:55:21,160 --> 00:55:23,550
Maybe $10,000 would put a dent. 

901
00:55:23,550 --> 00:55:26,810
But I can't not pitch in.
I'm still her daughter. 

902
00:55:26,810 --> 00:55:29,510
You are, but she doesn't care about you. 

903
00:55:29,510 --> 00:55:32,200
Tell those who want to show off pay for it. 

904
00:55:34,830 --> 00:55:35,850
Hey, 

905
00:55:36,990 --> 00:55:38,770
isn't that your brother in law? 

906
00:55:41,820 --> 00:55:42,920
Huh? 

907
00:55:44,500 --> 00:55:45,690
Minjung! 

908
00:55:46,850 --> 00:55:48,000
Minjung! 

909
00:55:55,940 --> 00:55:57,860
What are you going to do? 

910
00:55:58,750 --> 00:56:03,430
So your company went bankrupt? Totally? 

911
00:56:04,540 --> 00:56:07,350
You have nothing at all left? 

912
00:56:07,350 --> 00:56:09,860
Wow, how could this happen? 

913
00:56:09,860 --> 00:56:11,870
How unbelievable. 

914
00:56:13,950 --> 00:56:17,360
Tell Subak. You shouldn't burden this alone. 

915
00:56:17,360 --> 00:56:19,350
She needs to know. 

916
00:56:20,190 --> 00:56:23,140
I'm trying to find the right time. 

917
00:56:23,140 --> 00:56:26,550
She won't be able to handle this. 

918
00:56:26,550 --> 00:56:28,540
I brought it up a few days ago, 

919
00:56:28,540 --> 00:56:30,540
and she said she'll die with our children. 

920
00:56:30,540 --> 00:56:32,240
She said she'll die? 

921
00:56:32,910 --> 00:56:35,400
I can see her do that. 

922
00:56:35,400 --> 00:56:37,400
Hasn't that crossed your mind? 

923
00:56:37,400 --> 00:56:39,760
That you just want to kill yourself? 

924
00:56:39,760 --> 00:56:41,190
What's wrong with you? 

925
00:56:41,190 --> 00:56:44,220
I would if I were him. 

926
00:56:44,220 --> 00:56:47,010
But you're really amazing. 

927
00:56:47,010 --> 00:56:49,670
How could start a parcel service? 

928
00:56:49,930 --> 00:56:51,830
I'd be crying, jumping into the river, 

929
00:56:51,830 --> 00:56:53,730
jumping off a building, 

930
00:56:53,730 --> 00:56:58,360
set myself on fire, and go nut... 

931
00:57:02,880 --> 00:57:03,820
I really admire you, Minjung. 

932
00:57:05,640 --> 00:57:08,560
It'll be hard but what could she do? 

933
00:57:08,560 --> 00:57:10,590
She's a mother.
She must get through it. 

934
00:57:12,800 --> 00:57:16,560
Subak's been through just about everything. 

935
00:57:16,560 --> 00:57:19,920
All sorts of things, like... 

936
00:57:24,170 --> 00:57:27,590
What do you mean by that?
What bad things? 

937
00:57:27,590 --> 00:57:31,630
What bad things has she been through? 

938
00:57:31,630 --> 00:57:34,710
Nothing, Minjung. She didn't. 

939
00:57:34,710 --> 00:57:38,660
Before she met you,
she was a student. 

940
00:57:40,520 --> 00:57:44,650
Sometimes things just come out of my mouth. 

941
00:57:44,650 --> 00:57:48,220
I'm sort of all over the place. 

942
00:57:52,800 --> 00:57:55,180
How could you crush my foot? 

943
00:57:55,180 --> 00:57:57,040
Oh, my poor foot. 

944
00:58:00,440 --> 00:58:03,140
You're such a blabbermouth! 

945
00:58:03,140 --> 00:58:05,410
Why can't you think before you speak? 

946
00:58:05,410 --> 00:58:09,600
Subak doesn't think of you as her sister,
so why are you covering up for her? 

947
00:58:09,600 --> 00:58:11,700
If I were you, I'd tell him everything. 

948
00:58:11,700 --> 00:58:13,700
He would go insane. 

949
00:58:13,700 --> 00:58:16,690
I'm doing it for Minjung, not Subak. 

950
00:58:17,260 --> 00:58:19,530
You're so concerned about Minjung. 

951
00:58:19,530 --> 00:58:21,820
Go live with Minjung, then! 

952
00:58:22,860 --> 00:58:25,350
Keep this a secret until he tells her. 

953
00:58:25,350 --> 00:58:28,570
Even with uncle, okay? 

954
00:58:29,300 --> 00:58:31,310
Let me ask my mouth. 

955
00:58:32,540 --> 00:58:35,460
Mouth, mouth. 

956
00:58:36,050 --> 00:58:39,380
This is the biggest crisis of your life. 

957
00:58:39,380 --> 00:58:42,020
What would you do? Huh? 

958
00:58:43,550 --> 00:58:46,720
This is nuts. 

959
00:59:02,660 --> 00:59:03,720
What are you doing? 

960
00:59:05,020 --> 00:59:06,560
My friends are going crazy. 

961
00:59:06,560 --> 00:59:09,910
I uploaded photos and they're dying from jealousy. 

962
00:59:11,050 --> 00:59:12,960
So what's the occasion? 

963
00:59:14,380 --> 00:59:17,280
You feel bad for firing the housekeeper? 

964
00:59:18,190 --> 00:59:20,720
I do and I need to tell you something. 

965
00:59:21,220 --> 00:59:23,160
Oh I have something to tell you too. 

966
00:59:23,160 --> 00:59:25,780
Next Saturday is my mom's 60th birthday. 

967
00:59:25,780 --> 00:59:27,140
You didn't know, huh? 

968
00:59:28,220 --> 00:59:29,140
No. 

969
00:59:29,560 --> 00:59:32,610
I knew it.
You can't remember her birthday? 

970
00:59:33,450 --> 00:59:35,470
Us daughters had a meeting. 

971
00:59:35,470 --> 00:59:38,210
We'll have a buffet dinner and send her on a cruise. 

972
00:59:38,210 --> 00:59:40,980
And she's getting a face lift. 

973
00:59:40,980 --> 00:59:42,100
What? 

974
00:59:42,790 --> 00:59:45,130
I'm looking for a European cruise, 

975
00:59:45,130 --> 00:59:47,210
and we're thinking of inviting 100 guests. 

976
00:59:47,210 --> 00:59:49,650
So it'll be $150 per person, cheap. 

977
00:59:49,650 --> 00:59:52,790
With flowers and orchestra, about $30,000? 

978
00:59:52,790 --> 00:59:55,850
No harp. They asked for a delivery charge. 

979
00:59:55,850 --> 00:59:56,940
I did good, huh? 

980
01:00:17,130 --> 01:00:19,420
Do you know what day next Saturday is? 

981
01:00:19,420 --> 01:00:21,420
I told you, my mom's 60th birthday. 

982
01:00:21,420 --> 01:00:23,810
It's my mother's first memorial service. 

983
01:00:25,280 --> 01:00:26,840
Oh, no! 

984
01:00:28,310 --> 01:00:30,340
Can't we do it another day? 

985
01:00:30,340 --> 01:00:31,380
What? 

986
01:00:31,380 --> 01:00:33,750
What do I do?
I've already made reservations. 

987
01:00:54,320 --> 01:00:56,200
We can't do that for her. 

988
01:00:56,200 --> 01:00:58,200
We can do something simple, like dinner. 

989
01:00:58,200 --> 01:01:00,480
You don't want to spend money on my mom? 

990
01:01:00,480 --> 01:01:02,710
It's not that!
We can't afford it! 

991
01:01:02,710 --> 01:01:03,880
Why not? 

992
01:01:03,880 --> 01:01:06,150
She's taking care of our kids! 

993
01:01:06,950 --> 01:01:08,720
I'm disappointed in you. 

994
01:01:11,920 --> 01:01:13,150
Subak! 

995
01:01:45,370 --> 01:01:46,580
Father. 

996
01:01:46,580 --> 01:01:48,330
Where were you? 

997
01:01:48,330 --> 01:01:50,130
Why didn't you answer your phone? 

998
01:01:50,130 --> 01:01:51,920
We were having dinner. 

999
01:01:51,920 --> 01:01:54,450
You have a very good life. 

1000
01:01:54,450 --> 01:01:56,880
It's not good at all. 

1001
01:01:56,880 --> 01:01:58,320
What brings you here? 

1002
01:01:58,990 --> 01:02:00,660
That's all you can say? 

1003
01:02:00,660 --> 01:02:04,470
I'm not in a good mood,
so please don't add to it. 

1004
01:02:04,470 --> 01:02:05,980
Hello. 

1005
01:02:11,400 --> 01:02:14,110
Did you see that?
"Don't add to it"? 

1006
01:02:14,110 --> 01:02:16,510
And a simple "Hello" to father? 

1007
01:02:16,510 --> 01:02:18,410
Stop that. Let's just go. 

1008
01:02:18,410 --> 01:02:21,720
Why should you?
This is your son's house. 

1009
01:02:21,720 --> 01:02:23,300
Go inside. 

1010
01:02:23,300 --> 01:02:25,200
Come in, father. 

1011
01:02:25,200 --> 01:02:27,170
Go in. You shouldn't mind her. 

1012
01:02:27,170 --> 01:02:28,750
Why should you? 

1013
01:02:29,270 --> 01:02:30,930
I have to go and catch the train. 

1014
01:02:30,930 --> 01:02:31,920
Minsuk! 

1015
01:02:31,920 --> 01:02:33,550
Go in! 

1016
01:02:38,430 --> 01:02:39,900
I told you. 

1017
01:02:39,900 --> 01:02:43,230
If you don't take him, I'd bring him. 

1018
01:02:43,230 --> 01:02:46,650
Take care of him and control your wife. 

1019
01:02:46,650 --> 01:02:49,420
I'll send the rest of his stuff soon. 

1020
01:03:06,130 --> 01:03:08,270
- Enjoy.
- Thank you. 

1021
01:03:20,120 --> 01:03:21,440
What's this? 

1022
01:03:21,440 --> 01:03:22,800
Black bean noodles. 

1023
01:03:22,800 --> 01:03:25,290
I know what it is.
Why did you order it? 

1024
01:03:25,290 --> 01:03:27,080
It's for father. 

1025
01:03:27,080 --> 01:03:28,040
What? 

1026
01:03:28,040 --> 01:03:30,040
Tell your father to come and eat. 

1027
01:03:45,440 --> 01:04:07,300
Subtitles by KBS World 

1028
01:04:07,300 --> 01:04:10,070
This is the third time you did this to me. 

1029
01:04:10,070 --> 01:04:11,710
- Pay up.
- Excuse me? 

1030
01:04:11,710 --> 01:04:13,700
This is different from what I wrote. 

1031
01:04:13,700 --> 01:04:17,220
How could you belittle someone who's proud of his job? 

1032
01:04:17,220 --> 01:04:19,540
You don't want to live with me? What is it? 

1033
01:04:19,540 --> 01:04:21,330
I did everything I could for your family. 

1034
01:04:21,330 --> 01:04:27,080
You might think he's an embarrassment,
an aged country folk, but he's my father. 

1035
01:04:27,080 --> 01:04:28,600
This is what being married means? 

1036
01:04:28,600 --> 01:04:30,770
What did you have to endure? 

1037
01:04:30,770 --> 01:04:32,090
I've always been discriminated against! 

1038
01:04:32,090 --> 01:04:34,490
You think you never hurt me? 

1039
01:04:34,490 --> 01:04:35,460
Hurt you? 

1040
01:04:35,460 --> 01:04:36,630
You did. 

1041
01:04:36,630 --> 01:04:39,180
How did I ever hurt you? 

